            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-4">France is located in Western Europe and is bordered to the North by the North Sea, to the Northwest by the English Channel, to the West by the Atlantic Ocean, and to the Southeast by the Mediterranean Sea. Mainland France borders Belgium and Luxembourg to the Northeast, to the East is Switzerland and Germany, to the South and Southwest is Spain and Andorra, to the Southeast is Manaco and Italy.</p>
            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">A few words about France</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">French tourism always has a strong attraction for domestic and international tourists. France brings tourists many interesting experiences and unforgettable impressions.</p>
